Size. The type specimens range from 2.4 to 3.7 mm cl, the largest being a male missing its major cheliped. Colour in life. Semitransparent with small red chromatophores, some forming diffuse transverse bands on the abdomen; antennular and antennal peduncles and tail fan with red chromatophores; chelipeds and walking legs mostly whitish (
Fig. 7
).
